// Help HELP \j This is a starting guide for new users of the application. It describes how you can use the application. The guide is composed of the following topics :- 
 * Who should use this App? 
 * How do I use this App? 
 * Chatrooms for Students 
 * Chatrooms for Instructors 
 * The Notification Board 
 * The Slider 
 * About Who should use this App? \jThis app is built for the use of instructors and undergraduate students in the Department of Computer Science at Addis Ababa University. Anyone who want to use this app should be an Instructor or a current undergraduate student in the department. \j How do I use this App? \jInorder to use this app you should first enter your ID number and password in the provided fileds and press the login button. After you login, you will see list of course names in a tab titled "Chatrooms". \j Chatrooms for students \jIn the Chatrooms tab, if you are a student, you will see the list of cources you are currently taking. You can click on any of the listed cources inorder to enter the cource's chat area. Your instructor will be the one who will administrate the chatroom. You can post and view messeges in the chating area. \j Chatrooms for instructors \jIn this tab you will see the list of cources you are currently teaching. You can click on any of the listed cources inorder to enter the cource's chat area. You will be the one who will administrate the chatroom; titled with the course name you are teaching. You can post and view messeges in the chating area. You can also delete messages from the chat area. \j The Notification Board \jIn the tab titled "Notification Board" you will be able to see notifications posted by the department. The notifications from the department are followed by tags, which imply for whom this notifications are. \j The Slider \jYou can slide to the right from the left corner of your screen to open the slider. you can perform certain tasks from this window.(such as view your profile, change your password, share this app or logout) \j About This app is developed by:- 
